AIRPORT SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Airport Solar, LLC ("Airport Solar") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Airport Solar generating facility ("Airport Solar Facility").
The Airport Solar Facility is a solar generating facility located in Lake County, Oregon. The Airport Solar Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by PacifiCorp.
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Airport Solar's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Airport Solar Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Airport Solar's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $376,250.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $31,354,17.
